ZCZC OE10
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
FRIDAY TO MONDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 102300 UTC
ON FRIDAY EVENING A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE WILL EXTEND SW
ACROSS THE FAR N OF THE PORTPATRICK AREA WITH LOW
PRESSURE IN THE S MAINTAINING A CYCLONIC FLOW ELSEWHERE.
HIGH PRESSURE THEN EXP TO BUILD MORE GENERALLY IN THE N
DURING SATURDAY WITH LOW PRESSURE PERSISTING IN THE S.
THE LOW IS THEN FCST TO TRANSFER SE INTO BISCAY ON SUNDAY
AS PRESSURE BUILDS ACROSS THE AREA FM THE W AND CURRENT
EXPECTATIONS ARE FOR A STRG RIDGE TO EXTEND NE ACROSS THE
W OF THE AREA ON MONDAY. STRG TO GALE FORCE WINDS N OF
54N ON FRIDAY EVENING BECMG WIDESPREAD ACROSS MUCH OF
THE AREA S OF 62N ON SATURDAY. WINDS MAY REACH SEV GALE
OR STORM FORCE IN THE FAR SW FOR A TIME ON SUNDAY MORNING
BUT MOD IN THE NW DURING THE DAY. GALES ARE THEN
CURRENTLY FCST TO CONTINUE MODERATING FM THE NW ACROSS
ALL PARTS DURING MONDAY
